1) Create project name p6

2) Create limitranges name app_limits for project p6 with below requirement

    LimitRange name: app_limits (name goes under metadata)
    namespace: p6               (namespace info also goes under metadata)

    Pod:
       max: cpu=4 , memory=4Gi
       min: cpu="200m",memory="256Mi"

    Container:
       max: cpu=2, memory=2Gi
       min: cpu=100m, memory=128Mi
       default: cpu=500m, memory=256Mi
       defaultRequests: cpu=200m, memory=128Mi

Doc Link: 
  https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.14/pdf/scalability_and_performance/OpenShift_Container_Platform-4.14-Scalability_and_performance-en-US.pdf

Go To Chapter:
  5.3. SETTING LIMIT RANGES

  There you ll find pod and Container limitranges yaml file

3)  vi limitranges and paste the content you copy from the document and modify per our requirement

4) Apply

5) check the status



6) describe the limitranges


